<paragraph id="8BCB369A491F0D20FF23BBECFD86F9D2" blockId="3.[151,536,1526,1551]" box="[151,536,1526,1551]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<heading id="D08381F6491F0D20FF23BBECFD86F9D2" box="[151,536,1526,1551]" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" reason="3">
= 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D19491F0D20FF09BBEDFD86F9D2" authority="Steph." authorityName="Steph." box="[189,536,1526,1551]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Diplasiolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="brunnea">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FF09BBEDFE55F9D3" bold="true" box="[189,459,1526,1550]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Diplasiolejeunea brunnea</emphasis>
Steph.
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCB369A491F0D20FF23B823FF77F892" blockId="3.[113,765,1591,1871]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FF23B823FD96F992" box="[151,520,1591,1615]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Notes. – 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D19491F0D20FF43B82CFD96F992" box="[247,520,1591,1615]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Diplasiolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="brunnea">Diplasiolejeunea brunnea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is a widespread neotropical species that is distinguished by ocellate leaves without hyaline margin, large lobules with a conspicuous, erect, fingerlike first tooth and an inconspicuous second tooth, and by deeply bifid underleaves with widely diverging, lanceolate lobes with acute tips (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE54B6B491F0D20FEE6B8CCFE4DF932" author="REYES, D. M." box="[338,467,1751,1775]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="145 - 180" refId="ref9023" refString="REYES, D. M. (1982). El genero Diplasiolejeunea en Cuba. Acta Bot. Acad. - Sci. Hung. 28: 145 - 180." type="journal article" year="1982">REYES, 1982</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D19491F0D20FE56B8CCFD68F932" box="[482,758,1751,1775]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Diplasiolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="bidentiloba">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FE56B8CCFD68F932" box="[482,758,1751,1775]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Diplasiolejeunea bidentiloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54CF8838491F0D20FEEEB8ECFE16F8D2" box="[346,392,1783,1807]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
collected by Allioni, is identical to 
<taxonomicName id="4C744D19491F0D20FFC5B903FF7CF8F2" box="[113,226,1815,1839]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Diplasiolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="brunnea">
<emphasis id="B900EA88491F0D20FFC5B903FF7CF8F2" box="[113,226,1815,1839]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">D. brunnea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The new synonymy was already noted by R. Grolle (in sched.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
